<BR>
<b>Tierokan Cheezthief</b>, Ranger of Tunare of the 11th season-<i>"CHEEZ a day keeps Tierokan at bay"</i> and <i>"Have you shaved your halfling today?"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaabidano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aabidano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 7:24:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Server selection</span><hr size=1> My main is on Veeshan, I'll agree it's a fairly unfriendly place sometimes.<br>
<br>
Lanys has probably the nicest people of the servers I've been to.<br>
<br>
Surfing the server boards would probably youor best bet.  There are buttheads on all of them though. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaabidano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aabidano</A> at: 5/31/02 7:24:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustarstrider001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Starstrider001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 406<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 1:33:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Server selection</span><hr size=1> First of all I recommend that you do a character transfer rather than starting over, that's insanity.  Second I can speak highly of Druzzil Ro, and also of Xegony.  Both are older servers with smart and experienced players and people are kind of both servers.  However, there are a few guilds I'm not too pleased w/ on Druzzil....but all the pallys from those guilds are nice *Scrith* :) <p><A HREF=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=125676>Kalerien Orelias</A><BR>56th rank Half-Elven Knight<BR>Guardian of Xegony, <AHREF=http://www.asa-tru.com>Asa-Tru</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelgadol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elgadol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/3/02 10:54:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Server selection</span><hr size=1> Transferring characters across servers means you lose all of your gear, correct?<br>
I wonder whats worse, starting over, or being naked at 54 on a new server with no friends and no guild?<br>
Though tbh starting over from scratch is a pain in the ass.<br>
All my little twinks are dressed up so pretty, =) <br>
problem is there its just no where for them to go on this server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/3/02 1:24:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Starting over naked</span><hr size=1> I've seen it done many times.  I've seen level 50s given banded armor and a FS weapon and sent forth to re-equip themselves.  Even without a guild or friends, it can be done.  Too much emphasis is placed on equipment anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Do you have any trade skills that can make you some money or help to equip yourself?    <br>
<br>
I can think of numerous progressions that would work with just a little bit of playing time.  True, you aren't quite as capable as a monk or bard starting from scratch, but a paladin has many weapons against the undead and they have been known to relinquish good weapons and armor.  <br>
<br>
Moreover, as you become known on the server, people will willingly help, without being asked.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufennyin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fennyin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/3/02 1:59:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting over naked</span><hr size=1> I like Terris-Thule.  Almost everyone I've met has been pretty friendly. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47424">Fennyin Ellies</A>, level 52 High Elf Cavalier</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/4/02 9:11:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15328.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting over naked</span><hr size=1> Public raids is where someone leads them on a constant base and posts a sign up where others can join.  The RL figures out what classes they need and fill in spots.  If you missed last weeks raid, you go on the following week's raid.  Mostly independents and small guild members go.  Most guilds respect the Public.  Pretty good system.  Hate, Fear, PoG, Sky (sometimes), Vox, Naggy, Vindi, Kael Arena and others I think by now.  I have been gone awhile.<br>
<br>
I liked e'ci very much but I sure love Firiona Vie.  Different world here.<br>
<br>
Try transferring your character.  I vote for E'ci if you do.<br>
